class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> constructRectangle(int area) {
        int w = sqrt(area);
        while (area % w != 0) w--;
        return {area / w, w};
    }
};
```

efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(sqrt(n))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: This solution efficiently finds the optimal width by starting from the square root of the area and decrementing until it finds a divisor. This approach ensures that the difference between the length and width is minimized, satisfying the problem requirements.

